main event: On September 7, 1951, personnel at Goose Air Force Base, Labrador, observed unidentified aerial objects for approximately 10 minutes.
interesting points: The sighting included three bright lights moving rapidly at an altitude of about 10,000 feet., The control tower confirmed the sighting reported by the NCO officer., A round luminous object with a bright white light and a halo of colored lights was seen hovering., Unidentified aerial objects made sharp turns and rapid speed changes., Several reports indicate multiple witnesses, including four enlisted personnel during one observation.
witness description: enlisted personnel stationed at Goose AFB
